## Troubleshooting FAQ

**Q: Port already in use?**
A: Kill the process: `lsof -i :{{FRONTEND_PORT}}` then `kill -9 <PID>`, or change the port in the config.

**Q: Database connection refused?**
A: Make sure Docker is running: `docker compose up -d`. Check the `.env` file has the correct `DATABASE_URL`.

**Q: Prisma client out of date?**
A: Run `{{PRISMA_GENERATE_CMD}}` after any schema changes.

**Q: Type errors after pulling latest?**
A: Run `{{PKG_MANAGER}} install` to pick up new dependencies, then `{{PRISMA_GENERATE_CMD}}`.

**Q: Tests failing on a fresh clone?**
A: Ensure the test database exists and migrations are applied: `{{MIGRATE_CMD}}`.

**Q: Hot reload not working?**
A: Check for file system watcher limits. On Linux: `echo fs.inotify.max_user_watches=524288 | sudo tee -a /etc/sysctl.conf && sudo sysctl -p`.
